CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 14, 1970, pg. 13 reads: "City Kings - Shown in a victory celebration at the Civic Arena last week are members of the Schenley High Spartans basketball team that captured the City League basketball title against Carrick. Seen holding the Maurice Stokes Championship trophy (center) are Head Coach Spencer Watkins, Assistant Coach Bobby Young and Schenley Principal Arthur Outen.  Also on hand to help congratulate the Schenley team were Ed Fleming, assistant coach at Point Park College and a former teammate of Stokes and Charles Cooper, (behind Outen) Director of Parks and Recreation for Pittsburgh and a close friend of the former National Basketball Association star...Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of Schenley High School basketball players including Maurice Stokes, holding trophy and Maurice Lucas holding ball; Head Coach Spencer Watkins, Assistant Coach Bobby Young, Principal Arthur Outen, and Point Park coach Ed Fleming, posing in Civic Arena celebration City League Championship
